<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1201,1227]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Orth, 2000 in Thomas, Orth, Horeau &amp; Dominique" authorityYear="2000" box="[723,833,1202,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Bessierus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doloris">
<emphasis box="[723,833,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">B. doloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: (1) penis lobes closer to each other, almost touching (
<figureCitation box="[640,807,1238,1264]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3d and 3e</figureCitation>
); (2) base of each penis lobe, on outer margin, expanded (
<figureCitation box="[160,241,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); (3) telopenis slender (
<figureCitation box="[506,588,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); (4) inner margin of basal 1/3 of forceps segment I straight (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1356,1274,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,1309,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Description. Male imago.</emphasis>
Length of body 
<quantity box="[679,766,1310,1336]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 4.0 mm, cerci broken and missing. General coloration: yellowish brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[480,544,1346,1372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[559,727,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
): light brown, tinged with orange between ocelli; upper portion of eyes orangish, lower portion black; ocelli white, surrounded with black. Antennae light yellow brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1437,1382,1408]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,327,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
) orange-brown, sutures darker. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[774,857,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
): membrane of fore wings hyaline, veins C, Sc and R1 tinged with yellowish, remainder of veins yellowish, lighter rearward. Legs broken off and missing. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1320,1437,1453,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,327,1490,1516]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3b and 3c</figureCitation>
): terga yellowish-brown, terga I light brown, terga II–VIII shaded with light brown, terga with light V-shaped area medially and laterally on anterior margin. Sterna grayish-white. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1216,1526,1553]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[186,1404,185,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1953]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imago of Bessierus riobranco sp. n. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. body, lateral view; d. genitalia, ventral view; e. penes, ventral view; f. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397236/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Figs 3</figureCitation>
d–3f): styliger plate yellowish-brown, forceps yellowish-brown, lighter towards apex; inner margin of basal 1/3 of forceps segment I straight. Penis yellowish-orange, close to each other, almost touching; base of each penis lobe, on outer margin, expanded; telopenis slender. Caudal filaments broken and missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" box="[199,634,1669,1696]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,517,1669,1696]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Female imago and nymph.</emphasis>
Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="197" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1093,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1706,1732]" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Etymology.</emphasis>
In honor of Barão do Rio Branco, a Brazilian diplomat, lawyer, historian, geographer, journalist, politician, and professor. Due to his diplomatic efforts, he managed to peacefully resolve several territorial disputes, consolidating the borders of modern 
<collectingCountry box="[562,634,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. One of his accomplishments was the addition of the territory of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Amapá State</collectingRegion>
, which became a part of 
<collectingCountry box="[497,565,1814,1840]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in 1900, after a diplomatic dispute with the government of 
<collectingCountry box="[1248,1328,1814,1840]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="197">France</collectingCountry>
. Name in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
